\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"rich snippets\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:23:\"Table of Contents block\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=106939\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:464:\"<p>Do you want to know how to create a table of contents in WordPress? Creating a table of contents (ToC) in WordPress can be tricky if you&#8217;re a beginner. Even if you&#8217;re an expert, using WordPress&#8217; default method can rob&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-table-of-contents-in-wordpress/\">How to Create a Table of Contents in WordPress (2 Simple Methods)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16012:\"<p>Do you want to know how to create a table of contents in WordPress?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Creating a table of contents (ToC) in WordPress can be tricky if you&#8217;re a beginner. Even if you&#8217;re an expert, using WordPress&#8217; default method can rob you of a few precious minutes you could spend doing other productive things.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll show you how to automatically create a table of contents in WordPress and easily customize it to save you time.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-why-is-a-table-of-contents-important-in-wordpress\">Why is a Table of Contents Important in WordPress?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A table of contents helps users easily navigate your post, enhancing the user experience (UX). Most readers simply want to jump to the section with the answer they&#8217;re looking for, and a Table of Content helps them do that.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another benefit of a table of contents is that it helps you drive up your clickthrough rates (CTR) in SEO. Articles with a table of contents are more engaging and interactive on search engine results pages (SERPs) because they are enhanced by jump links.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"294\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-serps.png\" alt=\"Knowing how to create a table of contents is important as it has many SEO benefits.\" class=\"wp-image-105094\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-serps.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-serps-300x126.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-serps-600x252.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Jump links are an excellent way to encourage visitors to click on your website and go straight to the section they’re most interested in. The high CTR signals to search engines that users find your content valuable, and as a result, your SEO rankings improve.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another advantage of tables of contents is that they can help you land the coveted featured snippet to get you maximum SEO traffic. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"449\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-table-of-contents-featured-snippet.png\" alt=\"A table of contents can help you land the featured snippet.\" class=\"wp-image-106963\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-table-of-contents-featured-snippet.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-table-of-contents-featured-snippet-300x192.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-table-of-contents-featured-snippet-600x385.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Search engines often pull listicle-based snippets of content to display as the featured snippet. The main reason is that lists (like tables of contents) and bullet points can clearly and concisely communicate answers to users&#8217; questions. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-how-to-create-a-table-of-contents-in-wordpress\">How to Create a Table of Contents in WordPress</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The biggest challenge with creating a table of contents in WordPress is that it can take a lot of time to manually add jump links.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Luckily, there is a way that allows you to automatically add a table of contents in WordPress and even customize the headings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this tutorial, we will cover both methods on how to automatically create a table of contents in WordPress using a plugin as well as how to manually create a table of contents using code.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With that said, let&#8217;s jump right in.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-how-to-create-a-table-of-contents-in-wordpress-using-a-toc-block\">Method 1: How to Automatically Create a Table of Contents in WordPress</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The easiest way to automatically create a table of contents in WordPress is by using the Table of Contents feature in All in One SEO plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\" title=\"AIOSEO - WordPress SEO Plugin\">AIOSEO</a> is one of the best WordPress SEO plugins in the market, used by over 3 million website owners. Aside from dozens of powerful SEO features, it also comes with an advanced Table of Contents block that lets you automatically create a table of contents in WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"311\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO is one of the best SEO plugins on the market.\" class=\"wp-image-100113\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo-600x267.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>The first thing you need to do is install and activate the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">AIOSEO Pro</a> plugin. For detailed instructions, please see our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\" title=\"Installing All in One SEO Pro\">step-by-step guide to installing AIOSEO</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you have installed and set up the plugin, you&#8217;re now ready to add a table of contents in WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Step 1: Add the AIOSEO -Table of Contents Block</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>To add a table of contents to your blog post, all you have to do is open the WordPress content editor and then click the <strong>Add block</strong> button.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, you need to select the <strong>AIOSEO &#8211; Table of Contents</strong> block:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"498\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block.png\" alt=\"To add a ToC using a table of contents block, click the Add block button and select the AIOSEO - Table of Contents block.\" class=\"wp-image-107256\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block-300x213.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block-600x427.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you click on the <strong>AIOSEO &#8211; Table of Contents block</strong>, it will automatically create a table of contents block with all your subheadings.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"395\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-1.png\" alt=\"The Table of Content blocks helps you automatically create a table of contents on your posts.\" class=\"wp-image-104817\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-1.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-1-300x169.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-1-600x339.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<h4>Step 2: How to Customize Your Table of Contents  </h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Not only does the Table of Contents block saves you time by automatically generating a table of contents, but it also has powerful customization features. For example, you can:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Customize the heading text in the table of contents</li><li>Choose to hide and re-order headings inside the Table of Contents block</li><li>Customize the table of contents anchors</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>To customize your table of contents, you need to click on the block&#8217;s options menu.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"701\" height=\"398\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block-2.png\" alt=\"You can customize your table of contents using the block settings. \" class=\"wp-image-107345\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block-2.png 701w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block-2-300x170.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block-2-600x341.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 701px) 100vw, 701px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>From here, you can choose to reorder items in the table of contents or hide certain items.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You&#8217;ll find other Table of Contents block customization options in the editor&#8217;s sidebar:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"362\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block-3.png\" alt=\"You can also customize your ToC by using the block options in the sidebar.\" class=\"wp-image-107347\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block-3.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block-3-300x155.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block-3-600x310.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Here, you can change the list style and other advanced design settings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you&#8217;re done customizing your table of contents, make sure to save your draft, and that&#8217;s it! </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Congrats, you&#8217;ve successfully added a table of contents in WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"create-toc-manually\">Method 2: How to Manually Create a Table of Contents in WordPress </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you don&#8217;t want to use a table of contents plugin in WordPress, then you can also manually create a table of contents in WordPress. However, the process can be very time-consuming.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s take a look at the manual steps.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Step 1: Create HTML Anchors</h4>\n\n\n\n<p id=\"create-toc-manually\">The first step is to add HTML anchors to your <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/header-tags/\" title=\"Everything You Need to Know about Header Tags and How to Use them for SEO\">header tags</a> or subheadings. These HTML anchors will serve as internal links that you&#8217;ll use to link your various content subheadings in your table of contents.</p>\n\n\n\n<p id=\"create-toc-manually\">To get started, click on any subheading in the content editor. </p>\n\n\n\n<p id=\"create-toc-manually\">Next, go to the <strong>Block</strong> settings in the sidebar and scroll down to the <strong>Advanced</strong> section. Then, type in your tag in the <strong>HTML anchor</strong> field.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"699\" height=\"338\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-table-of-contents-in-wordpress-manually-html-anchors-1.png\" alt=\"Knowing how to create a table of contents in WordPress involves adding HTML anchors to your heading tags.\" class=\"wp-image-108375\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-table-of-contents-in-wordpress-manually-html-anchors-1.png 699w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-table-of-contents-in-wordpress-manually-html-anchors-1-300x145.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-table-of-contents-in-wordpress-manually-html-anchors-1-600x290.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 699px) 100vw, 699px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Your HTML anchor should be similar to your subheading. This will help you remember the HTML anchor associated with each subheading.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Step 2: Create a Table of Contents Using a Regular Content Block</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve created your HTML anchors, you can now create your table of contents.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>First, add a <strong>Paragraph</strong> block where you want to display your table of contents and title it accordingly.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, add a <strong>List</strong> block where you&#8217;ll list all your subheadings. You can either type them out or copy and paste them.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"699\" height=\"235\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-table-of-contents-in-wordpress-manually-list.png\" alt=\"Create a table of contents by adding a paragraph entitled &quot;Table of Contents&quot; and then list your subheads under it.\" class=\"wp-image-108360\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-table-of-contents-in-wordpress-manually-list.png 699w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-table-of-contents-in-wordpress-manually-list-300x101.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-table-of-contents-in-wordpress-manually-list-600x202.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 699px) 100vw, 699px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>This will serve as your table of contents.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Step 3: Link Your Sub-headings inside the Table of Contents </h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you&#8217;re done creating your table of contents listing, the next step is to link it to your subheadings using the HTML anchors you created.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To do that, highlight a list item in the table of contents and click on the <strong>Link</strong> icon.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"479\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-manually-3.png\" alt=\"Type in the HTML anchor and make sure to precede it with a hashtag (#).\" class=\"wp-image-107251\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-manually-3.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-manually-3-300x205.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-manually-3-600x411.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, type in the HTML anchor corresponding to the subheading you&#8217;re linking to and make sure to precede it with a hashtag (#). Once done, click on the <strong>Enter</strong> icon (or hit <strong>Enter</strong> on your keyboard), and the HTML anchor will be added to your table of contents list.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Repeat the process for the rest of the items on your table of contents.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As you&#8217;ll notice through the process, if your table of contents is long, then this can be quite time-consuming. That&#8217;s why we always recommend using our Table of Contents block. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article has helped you know how to add a table of contents in WordPress easily. Once you’re done, you may also want to check out some of our tutorials. A great example is our guide on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-2-super-easy-ways/\" title=\"How to Add an FAQ Section in WordPress (2 Super Easy Ways)\">how to add an FAQ section in WordPress</a>. You may also want to check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/link-building-guide/\" title=\"The Ultimate Link Building Guide You Need for 2022\">ultimate link building guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">YouTube Channel</a>. You’ll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/76569804/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://m.facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>  </p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-table-of-contents-in-wordpress/\">How to Create a Table of Contents in WordPress (2 Simple Methods)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-table-of-contents-in-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"How to Add an FAQ Section in WordPress (2 Super Easy Ways)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:176:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-2-super-easy-ways/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-2-super-easy-ways\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:84:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-2-super-easy-ways/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 28 Jul 2022 13:14:16 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"faq schema\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"FAQ section in WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"rich snippets\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=106698\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:460:\"<p>Do you want to know how to add an FAQ section in WordPress? FAQs are a powerful way to boost your search engine optimization. They enable you to get featured in Google&#8217;s &#8220;People Also Ask&#8221; section as well as get&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-2-super-easy-ways/\">How to Add an FAQ Section in WordPress (2 Super Easy Ways)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14321:\"<p>Do you want to know how to add an FAQ section in WordPress?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>FAQs are a powerful way to boost your search engine optimization. They enable you to get featured in Google&#8217;s &#8220;People Also Ask&#8221; section as well as get more prominent listings (rich snippets) in search engine results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll show you how to properly add an FAQ section in WordPress with FAQ schema output to boost your SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Why is an FAQ Section Important to Your SEO?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Having an FAQ section in your content is crucial to your SEO and can help boost your SEO rankings. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>One reason is that it helps improve user experience (UX) by providing users with answers to their questions. As a result, they stay longer on your site, signaling to search engines that your content is valuable. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another reason is that FAQs improve your visibility on SERPs, especially if they output JSON schema. This is because schema markup helps you get rich snippets that look more attractive than other search results. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the case of FAQ schema, it results in your search result looking bigger and more prominent than other results, as in the example below:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"474\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-serps.png\" alt=\"FAQs help you get rich results on search engine results pages.\" class=\"wp-image-105091\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-serps.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-serps-300x203.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-serps-600x406.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Search results like this also help show users that your content has the answers they&#8217;re looking for, thereby increasing your clickthrough rates (CTR). This signals to search engines that users love your content. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>How to Add an FAQ Section in WordPress (2 Easy Ways)</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Adding an FAQ section with proper schema markup in WordPress is pretty easy if you have a powerful WordPress SEO plugin like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">All In One SEO</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s why the first step in adding an FAQ section in WordPress should be to install AIOSEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"311\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO is one of the best SEO plugins on the market.\" class=\"wp-image-100113\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo-600x267.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"AIOSEO\">AIOSEO</a> is one of the best WordPress SEO plugins on the market and has been downloaded over 100 million times. Savvy marketers use the plugin to boost their search rankings and drive tons of traffic to their sites. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>For detailed instructions on installing AIOSEO, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\" title=\"Installing All in One SEO Pro\">check out our installation guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, let&#8217;s quickly look at two ways you can add an FAQ section in WordPress with AIOSEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Method 1: How to Add an FAQ Section in WordPress Using an FAQ Block</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The easiest way to add an FAQ section with proper FAQ schema is by using the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-aioseo-4-2-3-faq-and-table-of-contents-blocks-all-new-url-slug-monitor/\" title=\"Introducing AIOSEO 4.2.3 — FAQ and Table of Contents Blocks + All New URL Slug Monitor\">AIOSEO&#8217;s FAQ block</a>. This easy tool allows you to add an FAQ section to your content without going through the hoops of manually adding schema markup.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can use it to add an FAQ section on any page or blog post on your site, so you can get rich snippets in Google search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Step 1: Add the AIOSEO &#8211; FAQ Block</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>To add an FAQ section, simply add the <strong>AIOSEO &#8211; FAQ</strong> block in the WordPress content editor as you would any other block:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"699\" height=\"515\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block.png\" alt=\"Knowing how to add an FAQ section in WordPress is easy with our FAQ block.\" class=\"wp-image-106777\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block.png 699w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block-300x221.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block-600x442.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 699px) 100vw, 699px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, you need to add the frequently asked questions related to your content or web page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you add FAQs in this block, it will automatically create proper FAQ schema.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"699\" height=\"254\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block-2.png\" alt=\"Add your questions and answers in the fields provided. The questions have an H3 tag by default.\" class=\"wp-image-106787\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block-2.png 699w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block-2-300x109.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block-2-600x218.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 699px) 100vw, 699px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Go ahead and repeat this step for as many frequently asked questions that you would like to add to the post or page.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Step 2: Customize Your FAQ Section (Optional)</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO&#8217;s FAQ block has design options to help you customize the block’s background, text color, font size, and heading styles.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To customize your FAQ section, go to the block settings in the sidebar and expand the <strong>FAQ Options</strong> panel. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"406\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-options.png\" alt=\"You can customize the AIOSEO FAQ block any way you want.\" class=\"wp-image-105254\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-options.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-options-300x174.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-options-600x348.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>From here, you can select your text and background colors, typography and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Step 4: Set Your Visibility Status </h4>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO&#8217;s FAQ block also allows you to hide the FAQ section (or select FAQs) on the front end of your site while still outputting the JSON schema markup. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>By default, your FAQs are visible, so users can see them on the front end. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"699\" height=\"259\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block-visibility.png\" alt=\"You can choose to hide the FAQ section or parts of it on the front end by turning the Visibility toggle to the off position.\" class=\"wp-image-106788\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block-visibility.png 699w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block-visibility-300x111.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block-visibility-600x222.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 699px) 100vw, 699px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>To hide your FAQ section, simply turn the <strong>Visibility</strong> toggle to the off position. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>While users may not be able to see your FAQs, search engines can still read the schema markup, resulting in you getting rich snippets.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And that&#8217;s it!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You have successfully added an FAQ section to any WordPress post or page.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Method 2: How to Create a Dedicated FAQ Page + Schema Markup</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you&#8217;re running an <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-start-an-online-store/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"How to Start an Online Store\">online store</a> or a product website, then you may want to create a dedicated FAQ page on your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO comes with built-in support for dedicated FAQ page schema as well as a way for you to manually add custom schema markup.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s how you can use it to create a FAQ page.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Step 1: Create an FAQ Page in WordPress</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Simply open the WordPress block editor to create a New page and call it FAQs or Frequently Asked Questions.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the block editor, you can add all the frequently asked questions that you would like to add by typing them out as regular content blocks.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Depending on the structure of your content, you can add the appropriate <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/header-tags/\" title=\"Everything You Need to Know about Header Tags and How to Use them for SEO\">heading tag</a> (e.g., H3 or  H4) to the questions.   </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"333\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-content-block.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-107919\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-content-block.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-content-block-300x143.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-content-block-600x285.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The only drawback of this method is that you&#8217;ll also have to manually add the FAQ schema to the page. </p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Step 2: Add FAQ Schema</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>To add FAQ schema to your page, scroll down to the <strong>AIOSEO Settings</strong> and click on <strong>Schema</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"305\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress.png\" alt=\"You can manually add FAQ schema to your content by using AIOSEO\'s schema markup feature.\" class=\"wp-image-106705\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-300x131.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-600x261.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, set your schema type to <strong>Web Page</strong>, and then your <strong>Web Page Type</strong> to <strong>FAQ Page.</strong> Doing so will open a window where you can type in your questions and answers.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"440\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-content-block-2.png\" alt=\"Enter your questions and answers in the fields provided. Click on Add New to add another FAQ.\" class=\"wp-image-107920\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-content-block-2.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-content-block-2-300x189.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-content-block-2-600x377.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To add another FAQ, click on the <strong>Add New</strong> button. Repeat the process until you&#8217;ve added all your FAQs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once done, you can either save your draft or hit publish. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>And that&#8217;s it! You have manually added an FAQ section and FAQ schema to your article. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-faq-schema-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Add FAQ Schema in WordPress [The Easiest Way]\">Check out this guide</a> for more detailed step-by-step instructions on how to use this method to add schema markup to your WordPress posts and pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article has helped you know how to add an FAQ block in WordPress easily. Once you’re done, you may also be interested in our other guides. For example, you may want to know how to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/add-social-media-profiles-to-your-wordpress-sites-schema/\" title=\"How to Add Social Media Profiles to Your WordPress Site’s Schema\">add social media profiles to your site&#8217;s schema</a>. Or perhaps you may be interested in our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/blog-post-seo-checklist/\" title=\"A Complete Blog Post SEO Checklist to Boost Rankings\">blog post SEO checklist</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">YouTube Channel</a>. You’ll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/76569804/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://m.facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-2-super-easy-ways/\">How to Add an FAQ Section in WordPress (2 Super Easy Ways)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:81:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-2-super-easy-ways/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"How to Properly Set Up SEO for Different Languages and Countries\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:174:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-set-up-seo-for-different-languages-and-countries/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-s